episodes.description:
As part of a series on religious 'boot camps' and reform schools, MARK from Talk Beliefs presents a photo-illustrated interview with Gyl Maiersdorf from his home in Berlin, Germany, about his time in the Escuela Caribe Christian 'behavioural modification camp' in the Dominican Republic.

The bizarre twist to this tale is that Gyl was raised Jewish, and yet was sent to the Christian camp by his Jewish parents. Both he and his sister endured harsh disciplines and humiliation in an unregulated, military-style religious school whose methods go far beyond what might be called 'Christian'.

Support for anyone who has survived religious modification camps can be found through the SIA organization http://www.sia-now.org/


