Interview with JODI HOBBS, president of SIA (http://sia-now.org)

Jodi is a survivor of Victory Christian Academy, a youth treatment facility that once operated in Ramona, California. The facility was closed in 1991 after reports of mistreatment of children. Jodi formed SIA to help those affected by harmful treatment in behavioral modification type programs. 

Here, Jodi tells her story in graphic detail, describing relentless routines and harsh penalties endured by teens tricked by their own parents and sent away to what are effectively evangelical boot camps.

